Pseudo-code for Coalescing Contiguous Free Blocks

Algorithm: CoalesceFreeBlocks(free_list_ptr)
1. Set current = free_list_ptr
2. While current != NULL and current->next != NULL:
      a. Let next_block = current->next
      b. If current and next_block are contiguous in memory:
            i. Merge them:
                 current->size = current->size + next_block->size + sizeof(struct header)
            ii. Update links:
                 current->next = next_block->next
            iii. (Optional) Free(next_block)
      c. Else:
            current = current->next
3. End while
4. Return

